"script": "A single ballpoint pen can draw a line nearly two miles long, yet it never leaks in your pocket. So how does it lay down ink so smoothly? At the very tip sits a tiny metal ball, cradled in a socket but free to spin. As you drag the pen, the ball rolls and picks up thick ink from the reservoir behind it. Then it rolls that ink onto the page, just like a paint roller. And the ink is sticky enough to grip the ball, yet thin enough to flow. That balance is the whole secret.",
